HEADWORD: Crackled
<hw>Crac"kled</hw> <pr>(-k'ld)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Fine
Arts)</fld> <def>Covered with minute cracks in the glaze; -- said of
some kinds of porcelain and fine earthenware.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

